461–Male":"1461–Overleden","1463–Female":"1463–Overleden","1465–Female":"1465–Overleden","1468–Male":"1468–Overleden","–1521":"–1521","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1497–Female":"1497–Overleden","1498–Female":"1498–Overleden","1435–1487":"1435–1487","1437–1491":"1437–1491","1550":"1550","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1469":"1469","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1456":"1456","1521":"1521","1487":"1487","1498":"1498","1454":"1454","1465":"1465","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","1518":"1518","England":"England","London, England":"London, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bishop's Lynn, Norfolk, England":"King's Lynn, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1469–1518":"1469–1518","1456–Female":"1456–Deceased","1459–Male":"1459–Deceased","1460–Male":"1460–Deceased","1461–Male":"1461–Deceased","1463–Female":"1463–Deceased","1465–Female":"1465–Deceased","1468–Male":"1468–Deceased","–1521":"–1521","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1497–Female":"1497–Deceased","1498–Female":"1498–Deceased","1435–1487":"1435–1487","1437–1491":"1437–1491","1550":"1550","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1469":"1469","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1456":"1456","1521":"1521","1487":"1487","1498":"1498","1454":"1454","1465":"1465","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","1518":"1518","England":"England","London, England":"London, England, United Kingdom","Bishop's Lynn, Norfolk, England":"King's Lynn, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kinne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: from the female personal name <i>Kinne</i>, a Silesian pet form of Middle High German <i>Kunigunde</i>, composed of the Old High German elements <i>kuoni</i> ‘brave’ + <i>gund</i> ‘battle’.","Flemish: variant of   Kin   2 and 3."],"variants":[{"name":"Kin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Korean Sang, Young, Chong, Chun, Hak, Kwang, Song, Tae Wan, Yong, Yung, Aeja, Chin, Chul, Dong Joo, Dongil, Doo, Eng, Hee Chul, Hyeok, Hyung Joon, In-Young, Jong Woo, Min, Moon.","Polish: unexplained.","Dutch and Flemish: nickname for someone with a pointed or jutting chin, from Middle Dutch <i>kinne</i> ‘chin’."]}]},{"name":"Charles","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Germanic word, <i>karl</i>, meaning ‘free man’, akin to Old English <i>ceorl</i> ‘man’. The name, Latin form <i>Carolus</i>, owed its popularity in medieval Europe to the Frankish leader  Charlemagne  (  ?742–814 ), who in  800  established himself as Holy Roman Emperor. His name (Latin <i>Carolus Magnus</i>) means ‘Charles the Great’. <i>Carolus</i>—or <i>Karl</i>, the German form—was a common name among Frankish leaders, including Charlemagne's grandfather  Charles Martel  (  688–741 ). <i>Charles</i> is the French form. The name occurs occasionally in medieval Britain as <i>Karolus</i> or <i>Carolus</i>; it had a certain vogue in West Yorkshire from the 1400s, particularly among gentry families. The form <i>Charles</i> was chosen by  Mary Queen  of Scots (  1542–87 ), who had been brought up in France, for her son, <i>Charles James</i> (  1566–1625 ), who became  King James VI  of Scotland and, from  1603 ,  James I  of England. His son and grandson both reigned as  King Charles , and the name thus became established in the 17th century both in the Stuart royal house and among English and Scottish supporters of the Stuart monarchy. In the 18th century it was to some extent favoured, along with   James  , by Jacobites, supporters of the exiled Stuarts, opposed to the Hanoverian monarchy, especially in the Highlands of Scotland. In the 19th century the popularity of the name was further enhanced by romanticization of the story of ‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’, leader of the  1745  rebellion."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Charles Kinne was born in 1469, in King's Lynn, Norfolk, England, his father, Roland Kinne De Kene, was 34 and his mother, Sarah Clarke, was 32. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Ruth. He died in 1518, in King's Lynn, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 49."},"et":{"1469–1518":"1469–1518","1456–Female":"1456–Surnud","1459–Male":"1459–Surnud","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1461–Male":"1461–Surnud","1463–Female":"1463–Surnud","1465–Female":"1465–Surnud","1468–Male":"1468–Surnud","–1521":"–1521","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1497–Female":"1497–Surnud","1498–Female":"1498–Surnud","1435–1487":"1435–1487","1437–1491":"1437–1491","1550":"1550","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1469":"1469","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1456":"1456","1521":"1521","1487":"1487","1498":"1498","1454":"1454","1465":"1465","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","1518":"1518","England":"England","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bishop's Lynn, Norfolk, England":"King's Lynn, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1469–1518":"1469–1518","1456–Female":"1456–Kuollut","1459–Male":"1459–Kuollut","1460–Male":"1460–Kuollut","1461–Male":"1461–Kuollut","1463–Female":"1463–Kuollut","1465–Female":"1465–Kuollut","1468–Male":"1468–Kuollut","–1521":"–1521","1490–1550":"1490–1550","1497–Female":"1497–Kuollut","1498–Female":"1498–Kuollut","1435–1487":"1435–1487","1437–1491":"1437–1491","1550":"1550","1461":"1461","1460":"1460","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1469":"1469","1435":"1435","1468":"1468","1456":"1456","1521":"1521","1487":"1487","1498":"1498","1454":"1454","1465":"1465","1497":"1497","1463":"1463","1518":"1518","England":"England","London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bishop's Lynn, Norfolk, England":"King's Lynn, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1469–1518":"1469–1518","1456–Female":"1456–Décédée","1459–Male":"1459–Décédé","1460–Male":"1460–Décédé","1461–Male":"1461–Décédé","1463–Female":"